  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime involving $25,000, some of which has already been restituted. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, incarceration lengths are typically scaled according to the severity of the loss. A 10-year demand from a spectator is disproportionate to sentencing guidelines for a fraud amount of this scale. Therefore, a sentence of 6 months is deemed appropriate to serve as a sufficient deterrent while accounting for the defendant's lack of a prior criminal record and efforts toward restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
}
